<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idc9bf6e63-3a70-11f1-bde1-a5140e158598" identifier="/us/usc/t43/s316e"><num value="316e">§ 316e.</num><heading> Preferences</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">In considering applications to lease grazing privileges the Secretary shall, as far as is consistent with the efficient administration of the grazing district, prefer (1) natives, (2) other occupants of the range, and (3) settlers over all other applicants.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="idc9bf6e64-3a70-11f1-bde1-a5140e158598">(<ref href="/us/act/1927-03-04/ch513/s6">Mar. 4, 1927, ch. 513, § 6</ref>, <ref href="/us/stat/44/1453">44 Stat. 1453</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="idc9bf6e65-3a70-11f1-bde1-a5140e158598">
